Johannesburg – The Department of Basic Education has again urged teachers to get their vaccines. This after it emerged that about 9000 teachers did not want to be vaccinated. In a statement issued by the department today, they said that the rollout of the Johnson & Johnson vaccine would continue despite schools being closed. They said the sector had secured 289 000 more doses to vaccinate their target of 582 564 education staff. A total of 282 512 staff still require vaccinations. “In addition, support staff from independent schools, food handlers, screeners, cleaners and ECD (Early Childhood Development) practitioners will be included in the rollout program,” reads the statement. View the full statement below: <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-84454" src="http://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Statement-571x800.jpg" alt="" width="571" height="800" srcset="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Statement-571x800.jpg 571w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Statement-178x250.jpg 178w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Statement-768x1076.jpg 768w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Statement-1096x1536.jpg 1096w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Statement-696x975.jpg 696w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Statement-1068x1496.jpg 1068w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Statement-300x420.jpg 300w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Statement.jpg 914w" sizes="(max-width: 571px) 100vw, 571px" /> Also read: President’s daughter a vandal after ripping expensive clothes to shreds, claims ex Guptas stranded in Dubai as SA refuses to issue new passports Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. Sunday World 